  "chapter": {
    "number": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Woe to Those at Ease in Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to those at ease in Zion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and those secure on Mount Samaria,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the distinguished ones of the foremost nation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to whom the house of Israel comes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cross over to Calneh and see;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "go from there to the great Hamath;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "then go down to Gath of the Philistines.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Are you better than these kingdoms?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Is their territory larger than yours?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You dismiss the day of calamity",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and bring near a reign of violence.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You lie on beds inlaid with ivory,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lounge upon your couches.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You dine on lambs from the flock",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and calves from the stall.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You improvise songs on the harp like David",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and invent your own musical instruments.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You drink wine by the bowlful",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and anoint yourselves with the finest oils,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but you fail to grieve",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "over the ruin of Joseph.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, you will now go into exile",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as the first of the captives,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and your feasting and lounging",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will come to an end.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Pride of Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "The Lord GOD has sworn by Himself—the LORD, the God of Hosts, has declared:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I abhor Jacob’s pride",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and detest his citadels,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so I will deliver up the city",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and everything in it.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "And if there are ten men left in one house, they too will die."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "And when the relative who is to burn the bodies",
          {
            "noteId": 1313
          },
          "picks them up to remove them from the house, he will call to one inside, “Is anyone else with you?”",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "“None,” that person will answer.",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "“Silence,” the relative will retort, “for the name of the LORD must not be invoked.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "For the LORD gives a command:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“The great house will be smashed to pieces,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the small house to rubble.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Do horses gallop on the cliffs?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Does one plow the sea",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1314
          },
          {
            "text": "with oxen?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But you have turned justice into poison",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the fruit of righteousness into wormwood—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "you who rejoice in Lo-debar",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1315
          },
          {
            "text": "and say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Did we not take Karnaim",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1316
          },
          {
            "text": "by our own strength?’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For behold, I will raise up a nation",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against you, O house of Israel,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD, the God of Hosts,",
          {
            "text": "“and they will oppress you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from Lebo-hamath to the Brook of the Arabah.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 1313,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or to make a funeral fire to honor the dead",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 6,
          "verse": 10
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1314,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Literally Does one plow (there)",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 6,
          "verse": 12
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1315,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Lo-debar means nothing.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 6,
          "verse": 13
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1316,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Karnaim means horn, a symbol of strength.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 6,
          "verse": 13
        }
      }
    ]
  },
